{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id795db70d-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1112"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1112"},"text":"§ 1112.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Classification of goods and services; registration in plurality of classes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Director may establish a classification of goods and services, for convenience of Patent and Trademark Office administration, but not to limit or extend the applicant’s or registrant’s rights. The applicant may apply to register a mark for any or all of the goods or services on or in connection with which he or she is using or has a bona fide intention to use the mark in commerce: ","children":[{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided","children":[],"tail":", That if the Director by regulation permits the filing of an application for the registration of a mark for goods or services which fall within a plurality of classes, a fee equaling the sum of the fees for filing an application in each class shall be paid, and the Director may issue a single certificate of registration for such mark."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id795db70e-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1946-07-05/ch540"},"text":"July 5, 1946, ch. 540","children":[],"tail":", title IV, § 30, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/436"},"text":"60 Stat. 436","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/772/s16"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–772, § 16","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-10-09"},"text":"Oct. 9, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/76/773"},"text":"76 Stat. 773","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/596/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–596, § 1","children":[],"ta